description: Adorable, eco-friendly studio apartment, tucked in a lovely and peaceful garden setting in the Live Oak neighborhood. Close to Capitola, Santa Cruz, and the ocean. The studio has a full kitchen, cozy sleeping loft, outdoor hot tub, & more!    This adorable studio is perfect for one or two people. It has a cozy sleeping loft with a comfy queen bed, a full kitchen, a bathroom with a lovely tiled shower, walk-in closet space, and a sweet living room area with a vaulted ceiling.  Constructed using passive solar design, it stays just the right temperature all through the year and the south-facing windows and French doors allow light to stream in all day long.  On colder days, a radiant-heated floor system provides warmth by pumping water through tubing embedded in a beautifully-stained concrete floor, radiating heat through the rest of the house.  Finally, a photovoltaic solar system produces electricity from the sun!  The studio is nestled in a garden of winding flagstone paths, fruit tree
name: Lovely Garden Studio in Santa Cruz

description: Want to be pampered in a country, rustic setting?  This is the place for you. The two person slipper style copper tub is, by far, the main draw for many guests.  But the Cottage has a long history.  Initially it was the kiln for a potter who lived here before us.
